The peak stimulated emission cross-section σem is one of the most important radiative parameters and should be also examined because the strong luminescence band at 1535 nm due to the 4I13/2 → 4I15/2 transition has been considered as a potential near-infrared laser emission of Er3+ ions in fluoroindate glass. It is generally accepted that an efficient laser transition is characterized by relatively large value of σem. The peak stimulated emission cross-section σem can be obtained from the calculated radiative transition rate AJ using the following relation:8σem=λp48πcn2ΔλAJ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
