				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sigma _{{em}} = \frac{{\lambda _{p}^{4} }}{{8\pi cn^{2} \Delta \lambda }}A_{J}$$\end{document}where λp is the peak luminescence wavelength, Δλ is the effective linewidth (FWHM), n is the refractive index and c is the velocity of light. The maximum peak stimulated emission cross-section is close to nearly 5.4 × 10–21 cm2 at 1535 nm for fluoroindate glass and its value is typical for fluoride laser glasses containing Er3+ ions31.
